<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>
	
	<head>
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.0.0/css/bootstrap.min.css" integrity="sha384-Gn5384xqQ1aoWXA+058RXPxPg6fy4IWvTNh0E263XmFcJlSAwiGgFAW/dAiS6JXm" 			 crossorigin="anonymous">
		<link rel="stylesheet" href="../stylesheets/main.css">
		
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cairo:wght@300&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
	</head>
	
	
	
	<body class="show-body">
		
		
		
		<nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-dark homepage-navbar">
			<ul class="navbar-nav">
				<li class="nav-item">
					<a class="navbar-brand" href="/countries">Program</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
			
			<% if(!currentUser) { %>
				<ul class="navbar-nav ml-auto">
					<li class="nav-item ml-auto">
						<a class="nav-link" href="/login">Login</a>	
					</li>
				
					<li class="nav-item ml-auto">
						<a class="nav-link" href="register">Register</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			<% } else { %>
			
				<ul class="navbar-nav ml-auto">
					<li class="nav-item homepage-screenNameli">
						Welcome, <em><%= currentUser.screenName %></em>
					</li>
					
					<li class="nav-item">
						<a class="nav-link" href="/logout">Logout</a>
					</li>
					
					<li class="nav-item">
						<a class="nav-link" href="/account">View Account</a>
					</li>
				</ul>
			
			<% } %>
		</nav>
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-name">
			<h1 class="show-h1">
				Lithuania
			</h1>
		</div>
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center show-lesson">
			<h5 class="show-h5">
				Lesson 30
			</h5>
		</div>
			
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<img class="show-flag" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Flag_of_Lithuania_%281918%E2%80%931940%29.svg/220px-Flag_of_Lithuania_%281918%E2%80%931940%29.svg.png">
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-firstquickfacth4'>
			<h4>Capital: Vilnius</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Population: 2.8 million</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP): 55 billion dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		<div class='d-flex justify-content-center show-quickfactsh4'>
			<h4>Gross Domestic Product (GDP) Per Capita: 20,000 dollars</h4>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<hr class="show-hr1">	
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1 show-map" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/79/Lithuania_in_Europe_%28-rivers_-mini_map%29.svg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				The Republic of Lithuania is one of the Baltic States south of Latvia. For many centuries, the Baltic Sea was occupied by the Baltic tribes. In 1253 A.D, the Kingdom of Lithuania was formed, uniting all the tribes. During the 14th century, the Grand Duchy of Lithuania was the largest country in Europe and lasted until 1795, when the territory was annexed by the Russian Empire. In 1918, Lithuania declared independence. However, with the second World War, Lithuania was invaded by Germany, followed by Russia. With the Soviet Union’s dissolution in 1991, Lithuania gained independence once more.



			</p>
		</div>
		
		

		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.worldtravelguide.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/shu-Lithuania-Trakai-762676237-1440x823.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Trakai Island Castle in Trakai, Lithuania</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Today, Lithuania is a country with a good economy, high income, and high standard of living for its people.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Lithuania’s climate is temperate with cooler winters and summers. The capital Vilnius shows Baroque Architecture and has an old world charm with cobble stone streets.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://afar-production.imgix.net/uploads/images/afar_post_headers/images/BWTysEmbHQ/original_vilnius-lithuania.jpg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">
					<em><figcaption>Vilnius, Lithuania</figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		

		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<h3 class="show-factsh3">
				Two unique facts about Lithuania
			</h3>
		</div>
			
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				According to an ancient tradition - instead of the Easter Bunny - the Easter Granny, Velyku Senele, delivers easter eggs. The children leave their home made egg nests outside their doors, and in the morning they look for the treasured eggs.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<p class="show-text">
				Kūčios, the traditional Christmas Eve dinner, includes 12 different non-meat dishes, and there are no utensils. The food can only be eaten after the stars appear in the sky. The left over food is left on the table for ghosts to enjoy during the night.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
			<figure>
				<img class="show-img1" src="https://www.lithuania.travel/media/cache/widen_1100/uploads/mediaparkcms/article/c7ebfa74a8e0f3fce59b47cd7fac8b1d.jpeg">
				<span class="d-flex justify-content-center">Kūčios
					<em><figcaption>The Latvian Christmas Eve dinner </figcaption></em>
				</span>
			</figure>
		</div>
		
		
		
		<% if(currentUser && currentUser.lessonsComplete.length > 1){ %>
			<% currentUser.lessonsComplete.forEach(function(lesson){ %>
				<% if(lesson == "lithuania"){ %>
					<% lessonComplete = true %>
					<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
						<a href="/countries" class="show-returnHomebtn btn btn-light">
							Return to Program	
						</a>
					</div>
				<% } %>
			<% }) %>
		
			<% if(lessonComplete != true) {%>
					<form action="/countries/lithuania/account" method="POST">
						<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
							<button class="show-incompleteLessonbtn btn btn-success">
								Complete Lesson
							</button>
						</div>
					</form>
				<% } %>
		<% } %>
		
		
		
		<% if(!currentUser) { %>
			<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
				<a href="/countries" class="show-returnHomebtn btn btn-light">
					Return to Program	
				</a>
			</div>
		<% } %>
		
	
		
	</body>
	
	
</html>